description: Eid-ul-Adha, also known as Bakrid, is a significant celebration for Muslims globally. When Eid is observed depends on moon sighting, typically starting first in Gulf regions and later in South Asia. In 2024, it starts on Sunday, June 16, marking a day of sacrifice and redemption. here are 25 meaningful Eid Mubarak quotes and messages to send on Bakrid.
title: Happy Eid-ul-Adha: 25 meaningful Eid Mubarak quotes & messages

description: Babar Azam, the skipper of Pakistan, led his team to a narrow three-wicket win against Ireland in their final T20 World Cup encounter. His undefeated knock of 31 runs from 34 deliveries, combined with Shaheen Shah Afridi's stellar bowling performance of 3 wickets for 22 runs, secured the victory for Pakistan. However, the win was not enough for Pakistan to advance in the tournament, as they finished third in their group. Ireland, on the other hand, ended up at the bottom of the standings, having earned a solitary point from their rain-affected match against the USA.
title: 'It's tough times...': Afridi opens up on Pakistan's WC exit

description: A weekend shooting in a Texas park left two people dead and six wounded, including two children, authorities said. The victims were shot shortly before 11 pm Saturday during a Juneteenth celebration at Old Settlers Park in Round Rock, about 19 miles (30 kilometers) north of Austin. An altercation began between two groups during a concert at the event and someone started shooting, Round Rock Police Chief Allen Banks said during a news conference at the scene.
title: 2 killed and 6 wounded in shooting during Juneteenth celebration in Texas

description: Nikhil Gupta, a 52-year-old Indian national, has been extradited from the Czech Republic to the United States, where he is currently being held at the Metropolitan Detention Center in Brooklyn, according to the federal Bureau of Prisons website and a source familiar with the matter. Gupta is suspected by US authorities of being involved in a failed plot to assassinate Gurpatwant Singh Pannun, a US resident and advocate for a sovereign Sikh state in northern India.
title: Nikhil Gupta, suspect in plot to kill Pannun, extradited to US
